While researchers from the life sciences demonstrated the greatest interest, participation was highest from social and
Most researchers indicate no prior experience with the software and methods, impling that there is no institutional level
introduction to this material. But, more concerning are the scholars with some experience as they may understand the
importance of the software, but are not deeply skilled due to time, effort, or the abundance of choices and customization.
Of nine responses, all had positive recollections of the curriculum and found it helpful.
All respondents indicated that they are using the exact software, set up, and workflow designed in this curriculm.
Most have continued to use the persistent web-hosted materials and have introduced others use the materials
outside of this workshop. Some have even gone as far as to help others with the installation and set up.
All respondants specified that there was a scheduling conflict that prevented them from attended all of the
workshop sessions, while one suggests that the seminars are also too frequent (1 per week). Suggesting a monthly
session may yield higher attendance rates.
